<br />Well, the same goes for writing, which means that the need to buffer the data is a limitation of the system, not the compression scheme.
<br />
<br />But yeah, if you want to decompress tiles without turning rendering off you will need to buffer the data. This is not something I would recommend in a game with a lot of frame processing, it would be wasteful. If you do need to update tiles during gameplay, I suggest you keep them uncompressed.</div>

